Interesting. While I disagree with the political stance of the author, this is a very unfortunate location to set up a base. Hopefully, the planned relocation of American troops from this area will be carried out carefully and reasonably quickly. I'm not quite clear just what aspersion Bahrani is trying to cast in his last sentence, however -- surely he doesn't think the United States is just destroying Iraq's archaeological sites for the fun of it, does he? Or was this all a Bushite plot to control the world's richest deposits of Sumerian ruins?



